(1) linear search algorithm and progrom in c
------------------------------
step(1) Begin
step(2) set[5]<- {10,20,30,40,50}
step(3) set i<-0
step(4) input seaching item
step(5) Repeat step 6 and 7 while i<5
step(6) if a[i]= item then
        print item found and loccation=i and exit
step(7) i<- i+1
step(8) if i>=5 then
         print item not found
step(9) end

(2) linear search program in c without taking input from an user.
-------------------------------------
#include<stdio.h>
#include<conio.h>
int main()
{
int a[5]={10,20,30,40,50}, i=0,item;
printf("input searching item...");
scanf("%d",&item);
while(i<5)
{
if(a[i]==item)
{
printf("item found location=%d",i);
break;
}
i++;
}
if(i>=5)
printf("item not found");
getch();
}
